pqueue.lists

Class DoublyLinkedList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • pqueue.lists.LinkedList<T>
      • pqueue.lists.DoublyLinkedList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The data type held by the list.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, List<T>

    public class DoublyLinkedList<T>
extends LinkedList<T>

    A DoublyLinkedList is a LinkedList whose nodes have two references, one pointing to the previous and one to the next nodes.

    You should not edit this class! It is given to you as a resource for your project.

    Author:
    Jason Filippou
    See Also:
    StaticArrayList, LinkedList

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object other)
        Standard equals() method. Two LinearLists are equal if they contain the exact same elements at the same positions. Note that this equals() method allows for comparing different implementations of LinearLists, and potentially allowing them to be equal because they maintain the aforementioned contract! We are interested in ADT comparison, not 1-1 memory allocation comparison.
        Overrides:
        equals in class LinkedList<T>
        Parameters:
        other - The Object reference to compare to
        Returns:
        true if the two objects are considered "equal", with equality defined above.

      • get

        public T get(int index)
      throws EmptyListException,
             IllegalListAccessException
        Overriding of get(int index) for DoublyLinkedLists. This takes advantage of the structure of the list in order to optimize the search if the index of the element to be found is closer to either the end or the start of the list.
        Specified by:

        Overrides:

        Throws:
